Feature: “Scheduled Story Posting”

Description: Users should be able to create an Instagram Story and choose a future date and time for it to be posted automatically.
             This feature will help creators, businesses, and students plan content in advance without needing to be online at the posting time.


Team Members and Their Responsibilities:



Designer:  Design the scheduling interface, date/time picker, and confirmation screens. 
           Ensure the feature is easy to understand and visually consistent with Instagram’s existing design.


Backend/API Developer: Create APIs to save scheduled stories, store posting times, and trigger automatic publishing at the correct time.
                       Handle notifications and error cases.


Mobile Developer: Implement the scheduling UI in the Instagram app, connect it with backend APIs, and display scheduled stories
                  in the user’s drafts or scheduled section.


Tester (QA) : Verify that stories are posted at the correct time, test different time zones, check network failure scenarios,
              and ensure the feature works on various Android and iOS devices.
